 tos/aboutgallery3.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Since its inception in 1991\, the Skokie Festival of Cultures 
 has become one of the premier ethnic festivals in Illinois\, attracting mo
 re than a half-a-million visitors and dozens of cultures\, all representin
 g Skokie's tremendous diversity. Attendees can take a free 'Tour of the Wo
 rld\,' enjoying two days of ethnic folk music and dance\, a wide range of 
 food and beer\, unique arts and crafts\, a merchandise bazaar\, and dozens
  of cultural booths and displays.
LOCATION:Oakton Park\, 4701 Oakton St. \, Skokie\, IL
X-SOURCE:Visit Chicago North Shore
